==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cower
<hw>Cow"er</hw> <pr>(kou"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Cowered</conjf>
<pr>(kou"⟦etil⟧rd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Cowering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. Icel. <ets>kera</ets> to
doze, liequiet, Sw. <ets>kura</ets>, Dan. <ets>kure</ets>, G.
<ets>kauern</ets> to cower, W. <ets>cwrian</ets>.]</ety> <def>To stoop
by bending the knees; to crouch; to squat; hence, to quail; to sink
through fear.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our dame sits <qex>cowering</qex> o'er a kitchen fire.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like falcons, <qex>cowering</qex> on the nest.</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cower</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cower
<hw>Cow"er</hw> <pr>(kou"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cherish
with care.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cowering</ent>⟦br⟧
